12 ON ANY BOND OR COUPON CEASES TO SERVE IN AN AUTHORIZED CAPACITY BEFORE
13 THE DELIVERY OF THE BOND, THE SIGNATURE NEVERTHELESS IS AS VALID AND
14 SUFFICIENT FOR ALL PURPOSES AS IF THE INDIVIDUAL HAD REMAINED IN THAT
15 CAPACITY UNTIL DELIVERY OF THE BOND.
16 10.5–404.
17 (A) WITHOUT THE APPROVAL OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, AN AUTHORITY
18 MAY ISSUE BONDS TO REFINANCE ALL OR ANY PART OF THE COST OF
19 TRANSPORTATION FACILITIES OR PROJECTS FOR WHICH THE AUTHORITY
20 PREVIOUSLY ISSUED BONDS UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
21 (B) IF, BY REASON OF INCREASED CONSTRUCTION COSTS, ERROR IN
22 ESTIMATES, OR OTHERWISE, THE PROCEEDS OF THE BONDS OF ANY ISSUE ARE LESS
23 THAN THE AMOUNT REQUIRED FOR THE PURPOSE FOR WHICH THE BONDS ARE
24 AUTHORIZED, ADDITIONAL BONDS MAY BE ISSUED IN A SIMILAR MANNER TO
25 PROVIDE THE AMOUNT OF THE DEFICIENCY.
26 10.5–405.
27 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “REFUNDING” MEANS THE RETIREMENT AND
28 CANCELLATION OF BONDS, INCLUDING BONDS OF PRIOR ISSUES, AFTER THEIR
29 ACQUISITION BY OR FOR AN AUTHORITY, WHETHER BEFORE, AT, OR AFTER
30 MATURITY, EITHER IN EXCHANGE FOR OTHER BONDS OR BY PAYMENT, PURCHASE,
31 OR REDEMPTION WITH THE PROCEEDS OF THE SALE OF OTHER BONDS.
32 (B) AN AUTHORITY MAY ISSUE REFUNDING BONDS FOR:

